<collectingCountry id="9AE55FFCDAA5FF3E3887FCC49F47FCD9" box="[698,853,798,823]" name="New Zealand" pageId="178" pageNumber="179">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
. Adults are found in sheltered bays as well as deep offshore, associated with coral reefs; juveniles with floating debris and form aggregations, 
<quantity id="250AB289DAA5FF3E3E93FC98991AFCB4" box="[1198,1288,835,859]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="0.0" pageId="178" pageNumber="179" unit="m" value="10.0" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="0.0">
0– 
<specimenCount id="F4F4D4E5DAA5FF3E3EF7FC98991AFCB4" box="[1226,1288,835,859]" pageId="178" pageNumber="179" type="generic">20 m</specimenCount>
</quantity>
. Transitional water and marine.
</paragraph>
